reviews.review_text: This is the best laundry service experience ever. The receptionist was really helpful. She was very straightforward and made everything so easy. I didn t have Canadian cash and was unable to get cash from all those ATM machine. Fortunately they also accept U.S dollars and made the process so easy. Price was reasonable. I only spent $6 for both washing and drying. They don t have seats inside and the store is kinda small, but their service is too notch.

I use this laundromat for bedding and other things that my home machines cannot do, and there are always machines available at a great price. The couple who owns the business are always ready to offer advice on which machine to use and which setting for various types of clothing / bedding. Much better than other laundry options in the neighbourhood IMO.

I used their pickup/wash/delivery service yesterday and had a great experience. The price was fair, the person I talked to on the phone was friendly and helpful, and they also got a huge stain out of some of my stuff... Cant recommend enough :)

Really friendly and patient staff. Only downside is parking is hard to get by. There s parking behind the laundromat but it was hard for my camper van to get in because of cars parked on the other side of the narrow street. I parked in front of the store with the parking meter.

Great laundromat! The owners are so friendly and nice! Sadly there are hardly any laundromats left in Vancouver, and I hope they stay in business for many more years! I get a family run business vibe, they are hard workers and they are always busy doing tons of drop off orders but I ve never had an issue with needing a machine when I come in, have never had to wait even at busy times. They run their business very efficiently and don t put up with shenanigans. Everything takes loonies or quarters, but they will give you change at the till. Largest washing machines are $7/load, and the dryers are very fast. Usually a big load will dry in 30 minutes and cost $2.50 ish.

I really appreciate the nice woman greeting me and then showing me how everything works! It s funny, I never realized how much little things like this matter until I ve gotten older. THANK YOU!! Going to new places can be unnecessarily scary - your approach is greatly appreciated
Customer friendly staff. Price is reasonable.  Clean washroom. Big machines.  Busy locatiion. Morning is the best time during the week days. In & out 2 hrs.

Ive been using Launder All for my massage therapy practice linens for the past year or so. Theyve been consistently prompt and accommodating with delivery and the laundry is clean and professionally folded. The customer service amazing and I love that that its clearly family-owned. They take pride in what they do and it shows.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Natasha so much for your huge valued reviews and hope you are more successful in your next journey   keep in touch

reviews.review_text: I come here from the Hastings-Sunrise neighborhood about once a month to do all my laundry. I love their extractors. Its like an extra spin cycle for your clothes. I took a picture. It lessens the time your clothes need to be in the dryer. Just that convenience alone is worth the $1/load cost. Its also supposed to help your clothes not get worn out so fast. After my clothes have been in the extractor for all of a few minutes, I only need to run them through the dryer for about 30 minutes and theyre totally dry. They have a variety of double loaders, triple loaders and Jumbo machines for the washers. The dryers are huge and easily take my three washers worth of clothes in one. The people running the place are very helpful. Theres plenty of tables for folding and baskets for transferring your clothing. They have a change machine and a vending machine for laundry supplies. They seem to be one of the locations doing washing for the one of the hospitals? as theyre always doing massive loads of whites or what look like regular issue surgical scrubs. They have a wash and fold service for people too busy to do their own.

We went there to wash our duvets. The lady who works there was really nice helping us learn how to use the machines and giving us change because we didnt have enough coins. Big washers are $7 and the dryer costed around $2 for 30 minutes

The lady at the counter was extremely friendly. I havent finished my laundry yet so Im unsure of the results, but my experience was extremely positive.  She was very helpful and explained everything to me!

I own a healthcare clinic in Vancouver and this service has been fantastic. The owner has gone above and beyond for our company to ensure we have sheets and that they exceed our standards. They will pickup and deliver for commercial accounts which is very convenient. I absolutely recommend Launder All!
The best service you could ask for in Vancouver. Excellent service and help. You can not go wrong going to Launder All.
Great service. Friendly staff. My laundry done as requested. Always on time at a great price.

I needed my duvet cleaned and found their website. Unfortunately the pricing wasnt working properly online so I gave them a call and June was super helpful and was able to get us set up for a pick up and drop off quickly by text. Our duvet has just been picked up and they have been extremely flexible in setting up a drop off time for us! Im so pleased with this and assuming the duvet comes back squeaky clean (which I have no doubts about), I definitely anticipate using their service again.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind review, Chelin. We will continue the customer experience when placing order on our website. We hope to see you again.

reviews.review_text: They are  so nice, and have a great memory of their clients.

Amazing service. I have been using their pick up option weekly while our washing machine was broken. Communication was very easy, pick up and drop off was always on time. Clean laundry was professionally folded and sorted. I also loved their unscented detergent option. Highly reccomend.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Our pleasure   Thanks so much for everything   take care Maria and wish you and all your family the best

reviews.review_text: Their pickup and delivery service is amazing and makes my life so much easier. They do everything and fold them really nicely. Can be pricey if you go over weight. The service is worth it though.

Used the pickup and drop off same day service. They were very easy to communicate with, pickup and drop off directly from my hotel. The clothes are clean, dry and impeccably folded. Excellent service for the price. Highly recommended!

- washer $7, and using the dryer is $35 for 35min! - Customer service is excellent, and if you do not know how to use machines, they will help you or advise! - I am willing to go there again and use the service! Thank you for being friendly to customers! - After I am using the blanket washed at the laundromat, I feel my body is a little bit itch, but i am not sure this issue was caused by launder all coun laundry.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your review and we hope to see you again.

reviews.review_text: June is wonderful and always so helpful. Cannot recommend this wonderful little business enough.

Great dry cleaning services! Went there when my previous place closed for a month. Friendly, knowledgeable, great prices, with a super fast return rate. Plus open 7 days a week. Very happy with their services. Will keep returning
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for your kind review, Leela! We will be here to serve you when you come back.

reviews.review_text: Awesome! The owners are really nice people and the environment is nice. Good machines as far as I see and you get free WiFi while waiting.

It is a very good place to do your laundry very nice people run the place they are very helpful if you need it and always there for you. Happy joyful employees love the place I wouldnt go nowhere else even though I have to travel to get there
Best Laundromat EVER ! Super friendly. Fast, efficient machines. Always remembers my name and I only go 3 times a year. GREAT LOCATION !

LAUNDER ALL IS THE BEST! I have been bringing my laundry here for wash and fold for about two years now. The machines in my building are horrible, expensive and waste a lot of my time. For just a bit more, I drop off a months worth of laundry and pick it up either the same day or very next. Each and every time, I am met with amazing customer service and have been satisfied with the quality of work every single time! To be frank, running a laundromat during a pandemic cant be an easy feat and the sweet people that run it work nearly every single day. Id love to see more of our neighbourhood supporting them and considering using their services. Bonus: There is parking in the back of the building. Thank you so much Launder All for improving my quality of life =) - Linda
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for your valued reviews to us, Linda    we are always glad doing laundry for you

reviews.review_text: Brought my duvet blanket here to be cleaned. And it looked and smelt great. Big machines to wash big laundry loads. The staff are amazing here!

Donny was very helpful and friendly and knowledgeable. The laundromat was very clean and maintained in an orderly manner. The machines were very clean and maintained too. I highly recommend this place too because it is surrounded by cool shops you can go to while waiting for your laundry to finish washing and or drying. The machines are reasonably priced too. The drums are sized according to the size of ones wash.

I had an fabulous experience when I went to this laundromat.  I had never been here before and when I went in with my many bags of laundry I was wonderfully recieved by the attendant who was working  there. I think that she said her name was Judy(I am sorry I dont remember) she was very helpful as well as friendly. I feel that she went above and beyond the call of duty . Not only was the service friendly but also the place was very clean and organized. There is also parking at the back of the store. And you can sit outside in front of the store while you are waiting for your laundry. If you are hungry there are many places to grab a bite to eat.
Run down. But the staff very freindly and helpful to someone out of town.

I m a happy new customer who just started coming here for drop-off service (wash-dry-fold). While I m usually quite picky about who handles my laundry, June makes it easy to entrust her with your essentials. Whether you need help cleaning your clothes, towels, sheets, or even pet items, June will launder it all   and she ll do a great job, fast, for a fair price. Laundry is now my favourite chore!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Bella for your valued reviews

reviews.review_text: Took my king sized duvet in today and June had it ready by six pm. Love that she remembers my name and it came out so beautifully clean. Thank you June!

The girl working was super helpful and I was able to get my laundry done and feel a bit more accustomed to the facility now because of her help. The staff was very friendly and I had an overall good experience there! Also their machines did a fantastic job at cleaning my clothes!!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Ariel! We are appreciate that

reviews.review_text: Such a great service! No complaints at all, always pick up and deliver on time, and my clothing is always folded perfectly!
Great service! I use them occasionally for personal items and always for AirBnB turnarounds with lots of sheets and towels.

People write whatever they want these days its hard to tell whos telling the truth. So I came here today under the impression that they where both bad and good. And I can tell you its a laundry mat.. the washers and dryers work well and the staff is nice and informative. Same price as all the other coin laundry mats. Cant complain got my stuff washed and dried in a decent time frame.

wonderful laundry. very good friendly service. June and her husband are really nice people. The second time I went there I walk in the door and June said hello and my name! Now that is friendly neighbourly service.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much my pleasure

reviews.review_text: I had four loads of laundry and it cost me $7 for two huge washers and about $6 to dry totally worth it Ill go again south was amazing and friendly the place was clean and I was done my four loads of laundry  under 2 hours

Good laundromat.  Much more parking at nearby businesses on the weekend as those businesses are not open (ie. dental shop). The extractors are fantastic.  The best thing about them is they remove almost all of the grungy rinse water so faster drying with cleaner clothes. Heres how you wash everything for $9.50 $7 for the 5X washing machine at the very front or back (5 loads!) $1 for the extractor, balance evenly and spread a towel over top $1.50 for 24 minutes of drying And presto, you are home and watching opinionated people on YouTube

Had a great experience using the jumbo machines to wash a duvet that was too big for our own washing machine at home. Wash cycle was fast and thorough, large dryer was also excellent. Owner was very friendly and helpful, highly recommended!
Awesome service! The lady on shift was super polite and helpful. Washer machines are $3/$5/$7 depending on size. Dryers are 25 cent per 4 mins . Would recommend!

This is actually my first review and doing it because I am so impressed with how the owners treat you when you go there.  The level of attentiveness and interest is amazing and highly recommend going here.  I do the drop off service and always more than happy ... it is more about the feeling though they give when you go there though.  I have probably in my life tried 20 or so laundry places for drop off and this is # 1 for sure!
Great experience at this place today. Machines did an excellent job, prices are reasonable, and the staff is so friendly. Ill come back, definitely!

Paying an arm and a leg to use my buildings one washing machine and dryer I set out to find a local launder that was reasonably priced and convenient. I found Launder All Coin online and have been going there for the past 6 months with ZERO problems. The staff is super friendly, machines work great, its affordable, and when Im too busy and dont have time to do it myself their drop off laundry services are perfect! 5 stars!

They have large machines to clean my queen size duvet, a spinner that cuts down drying time, and very efficient dryers that dry much faster than my dryer at home.  The owners are very friendly, and the place is clean and bright.

Hello and good day to all,In todays hard time its hard to find a good service provider,And Launder All Coin you will find a full service facilities that will clean your laundry for you alterations sewing and repairs also they also provide dry cleaning services I highly recommend them thank you all please have a nice peaceful pleasant day.

These are the best humans and they are so very sweet and it is a lifesaver to be able to drop off my laundry.  Any time I accidentally decide to do a load in the Coinamatic machines in the apartment basement, I am reminded of how much easier and more convenient it is just to hand it over and come back later.

Nice, quiet, easy to use place to do laundry. Has change machine in case you dont have any which is super handy. There are carts for transferring everything. Tables for folding...and a cafe very near by! Shaw Wifi is also available.
love this place, great hours, clean and best of all very friendly and helpful. I come here from the downtown eastside to do my laundry. Its worth it by far. Especially the service!!!!!!!!!!
Great service, pick up and delivery, affordable price. Good for those who live in the hotels. Strongly recommend.
Very good service. Took care of all our laundry. We came back and everything was ready. Even the socks were paired. Very fair price. Highly recommended.
Huge thanks to June at Launder-All for exceptionally friendly and quick service.  Every time, i leave smiling.  Thanks.  Stay gold

The staff are always very nice, friendly and helpful!! :3 My first time going in, they noticed I looked confused and they helped me out through the whole process. It made the experience less stressful
Dropped off winter blankets and coats to be washed and dried.  Excellent, timely and friendly service.  Very impressed.

You walk in, there is no music playing, no clanging windchimes, only the sonic sound of a vintage Extrator Machine whirling like a F-14 turbo engine gunning on full thrust...impressive. ..Otherwise appreciate the helpful service, clothes are once again clean and I live another day to tell of it.
Each time I drop off a load of laundry, I m greeted with a huge smile and a genuine welcome. Inexpensive, fast turnaround time and honestly the best and friendliest service I could ever ask for.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Stephanie! We are appreciate that

reviews.review_text: I must say this is your best place to go do your laundry. It s clean and the staff there go way beyond their jobs to help you. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND GOING HERE!!

I first went to this place for the old fashioned extractors that spin the extra water out of your laundry.  In addition, the new owners are great.  The place is clean and organized and everything works.  Nice decor as well.

Not only did they wash and iron my shirt at super short notice but these guys are one of the only dry cleaners open on sundays (which was a lifesaver for me). Also the price was cheap! Im so thankful for the people at this place im going to be coming here from now on for everything I need washed. so good.
This place has the nicest, most friendly staff. They are always willing to help and offer services above and beyond.. Love the pick up and drop off service.

Launder all is the best dry cleaning in Vancouver!! Awesome prices, friendly staff, great neighborhood, honest people and the best part is I picked up my jacket that I knew had a hole in the pocket to find it repaired (or missing?) ! BONUS!! Go here.
I enjoy this place and the people there are friendly. A good turn around when dropping off my clothes to wash.

The women, assuming owner, sooo helpful! - Im 26 - Ive never done laundry before. Like literally never - My dad cooked. My mom cleaned up - Was expecting the whole thing to be a nightmare - She saved my - Nuff said -
Dryer broke down in my building, came 6pm at night. My loads dried in 24 mins, in that time spent time talking to the awesome people that worked there.
Clean machines and friendly atmosphere. Staff is always friendly and keeps a close eye on the machines, so stepping away while your machine does its thing is never an issue.

I really have no time to do my own laundry so I drop my laundry off at launderall and the ladies are very professional and my clothes are so properly folded and they smell nice I am so happy with this place I highly recommend.....

AWESOME PLACE..I do my laundry there all the time..The people who run it are the most friendliest people I have met..so easy to talk with and always helpful. I recomend anyone to this place.... Norm G.
Went to do all.my sleeping bags and fleece.set. very helpful.and friendly, thanks June! Will be recommending this place and return as needed.
Fast and friendly! Top marks!
I used UpOnDry.com and they got my clothes delivered to my house during COVID19. Great service by June!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your valued reviews

reviews.review_text: Extremely helpful and friendly staff! Reasonably clean, machines work well, convenient location.
Love doing my laundry here The guy that works there is very nice Also very helpful .the place is very clean .. Its a chill place to do your laundry
Quick and quiet for the time and day I went.  Id go again if needed.
Really friendly service. Lots of big washers. I had a great experience
Friendly owner, great machines at reasonable prices.
The owners are very kind! Prices are reasonable and the place is clean.
Clean, friendly service and fair prices.
Love this place! Always clean, reasonably priced, free parking in the back, and the owners are amazingly nice and always willing to help!
Very friendly and super helpful. Makes my life that much easier
Fair prices and great service!
Absolutely love this place. Everyone is so incredibly friendly and the do an amazing job.
Open late like every Laundry Matt should be, not to mention the spin machine that saves time money and drying time nice touch

we love them! always fast and reliable :)
